main event: Two bright red lights were observed in the sky near Orlando, Florida on May 15, 1965. The lights were stationary for about 1 minute, then moved rapidly overhead, turned and flew away to the northeast.
interesting points: The lights were accompanied by a humming sound, described as a motor-like sound.
The lights appeared to be one object at first, but as it got closer it became apparent that there were two lights.
The object was observed heading west to east, then turned and flew away to the northeast.
The object was estimated to be at an altitude of around 15,000 feet.
The sighting lasted for approximately 10 minutes.
